; traits.bl — compatibility shim (spec §6.4). The `Show`/`Ord` traits + dictionary-passing that used
; to live here now reside in `std/order.bl` (with `show`, `cmp`, and the `Nat`/`Bool` instances).
; This shim preserves the historical `(load "traits.bl")` entry point.
;
; `(import …)`, not `(load …)`: `order.bl` declares the `(instance (Show Nat) …)` — the only
; `instance` in the prelude — so `import` (idempotent; see `crates/blight-elab/src/program.rs`)
; keeps `(load "traits.bl")` safe to combine with any other module that also needs `order.bl`.
(import "std/order.bl")
